# 2p_multi_round — verify round 2 doesn't immediately end after
# round 1's score cap. The user-reported bug: "first round ends,
# map vote, then round 2 starts and IMMEDIATELY ends." Pre-fix
# advance_to_next_round didn't clear per-round slot.score, so the
# FFA score gate fired the same tick round 2 began.
#
# Plan: cfg score_limit=2 + rounds_per_match=3. Host scores 2 kills
# → round 1 ends → vote-driven summary fast-forward → round 2
# begins. Round 2 then runs WITHOUT additional kills until the
# round time-limit or our shot script ends — proving round 2
# stayed in MATCH_PHASE_ACTIVE rather than ending instantly.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/host_multi_round
network host 24043
name HostShooter

spawn_at 600 1100
peer_spawn 1 800 1100

aim 800 1070

contact_sheet sheet cols 4 cell 320 180

# Round 1.
at 140 shot t140_r1_start
at 200 kill_peer 1 0
at 400 kill_peer 1 0
at 420 shot t420_r1_summary

# Cast a vote so summary fast-forwards (BOTH sides must vote — see
# host_match_flow_step's "all voted" gate). Both scripts cast at
# the same tick.
at 460 vote_map 0

# Round 2 begins around tick 700 (~520 + 180-tick countdown).
# Capture a frame WELL inside round 2 to prove it's playing.
at 1200 shot t1200_r2_playing

at 1400 end
